A recent survey in urban Shanghai revealed high obesity rates among adults and children, mirroring developed countries.
Improved living standards contribute to the rising obesity trend in China, especially among city dwellers.
Lack of exercise, excessive sleep, and high-fat diets are major factors.
Men are more prone to obesity than women, with certain age groups at higher risk.
Despite health warnings, the government focuses on public lifestyle changes rather than imposing bans.
Similar concerns exist in Kuwait, where hypnotherapy shows promise in treating obesity.
In the UAE, diabetes rates are escalating due to obesity, emphasizing the need for preventive measures through education and healthy eating habits.
